public abstract class Lookahead extends Object implements Pattern

  • Method Details

    • find

      protected static ImmutableList<Token> find(Keyword keyword, ImmutableList<Token> tokens)
      Searches a list of tokens for the first occurrence of a keyword, and if it is found, returns the list starting at that token. This search will skip over tokens inside paired brackets, including parentheses, square brackets, and curly brackets. For example, if the list contains six tokens "a ( a b ) b" and the keyword to find is "b", the first occurrence of "b" would be skipped because it appears inside paired parentheses and the last token would be the one found.
      Parameters:
      keyword - the keyword to search for
      tokens - the list of tokens to search
      Returns:
      the list of tokens starting at the first occurrence of the keyword, or null if the keyword was not found

    • find

      protected static final ImmutableList<Token> find(String query, ImmutableList<Token> tokens)
      Searches a list of tokens for the first occurrence of a token whose string value matches a query, and if it is found, returns the list starting at that token. This search will skip over tokens inside paired brackets, including parentheses, square brackets, and curly brackets. For example, if the list contains six tokens "a ( a b ) b" and the query to find is "b", the first occurrence of "b" would be skipped because it appears inside paired parentheses and the last token would be the one found.
      Parameters:
      query - the token value to search for
      tokens - the list of tokens to search
      Returns:
      the list of tokens starting at the first occurrence of the query, or null if the query was not found
